0190037.fig13b.jpeg" height="1406" width="1482" aria-labelledby="fig13b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span>. Metastatic gastrointestinal stromal tumor in a 51-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Axial arterial phase T1-weighted MR image shows an enhancing tumor (arrow). <b>(b)</b> On an axial HBP MR image, the tumor (arrow) is hypointense, with a hyperintense rim, indicating peritumoral retention.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig14a.jpeg" height="1398" width="1475" aria-labelledby="fig14a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span>. Metastatic neuroendocrine tumor in a 65-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Axial arterial phase T1-weighted MR image shows enhancement of the tumor (arrow). <b>(b)</b> On a coronal HBP MR image, the tumor (arrow) is hypointense and surrounded by a hyperintense rim, indicating peritumoral retention.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig14b.jpeg" height="1398" width="1476" aria-labelledby="fig14b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span>. Metastatic neuroendocrine tumor in a 65-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Axial arterial phase T1-weighted MR image shows enhancement of the tumor (arrow). <b>(b)</b> On a coronal HBP MR image, the tumor (arrow) is hypointense and surrounded by a hyperintense rim, indicating peritumoral retention.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig15a.jpeg" height="1383" width="1471" aria-labelledby="fig15a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15a</span>. IPNB in a 52-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Contrast-enhanced CT image shows a cystic tumor (arrow) with a solid component (arrowhead). <b>(b)</b> Axial HBP MR image shows the cystic component—that is, the dilated bile duct (arrow)—to be well enhanced.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig15a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig15b.jpeg" height="1383" width="1479" aria-labelledby="fig15b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15b</span>. IPNB in a 52-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Contrast-enhanced CT image shows a cystic tumor (arrow) with a solid component (arrowhead). <b>(b)</b> Axial HBP MR image shows the cystic component—that is, the dilated bile duct (arrow)—to be well enhanced.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig15b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig16a.jpeg" height="1400" width="1472" aria-labelledby="fig16a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16a</span>. Malignant lymphoma in an 83-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Axial arterial phase T1-weighted MR image shows enhancement of the tumor (arrow). <b>(b)</b> Coronal HBP MR image shows enhanced nondistorted biliary ducts (arrow) in the tumor.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig16a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig16b.jpeg" height="1400" width="1478" aria-labelledby="fig16b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16b</span>. Malignant lymphoma in an 83-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Axial arterial phase T1-weighted MR image shows enhancement of the tumor (arrow). <b>(b)</b> Coronal HBP MR image shows enhanced nondistorted biliary ducts (arrow) in the tumor.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig16b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190037/asset/images/large/rg.2020190037.fig17.jpeg" height="2025" width="2700" aria-labelledby="fig17" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17</span>. Diagram summarizes the differential diagnosis of hyperintense liver masses seen during the HBP. <i>GIST</i> = gastrointestinal stromal tumor, <i>NET</i> = neuroendocrine tumor.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190037&amp;id=fig17">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div cl